title: How New York civil fraud ruling could affect Trump's finances
description: A judge's ruling in Donald Trump's civil fraud trial dealt a serious blow to the former president's finances. The GOP frontrunner and the Trump Organization were ordered to pay penalties of more than $354 million. CBS News campaign reporter Katrina Kaufman has more.

title: Haley campaigns in South Carolina as Trump slams legal cases in pitch to voters
description: Former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley campaigns in South Carolina ahead of the Republican primary. With five days to go, former President Donald Trump is leading the polls and over the weekend brought up his legal troubles in a speech to Michigan voters. CBS News political correspondent Caitlin Huey-Burns and campaign reporter Olivia Rinaldi have the latest from the campaign trail.

title: Nikki Haley back in South Carolina for campaign stops ahead of GOP primary
description: Donald Trump is polling ahead of Nikki Haley by double digits in South Carolina, but Haley, the former governor of the state, is back on the ground there trying to make a dent with just days remaining until the Republican primary. CBS News campaign reporter Olivia Rinaldi has more on the race in South Carolina and the Trump campaign's look ahead to the general election.

title: Supreme Court could rule on 2 Trump cases this week
description: The Supreme Court could issue rulings related to Donald Trump's immunity claim in a federal case and his ballot eligibility case in Colorado as soon as this week. Attorney and CBS News campaign reporter Katrina Kaufman has more on how the high court may be approaching the two decisions.

title: Suspect arrested in Colorado dorm killings
description: Police have arrested a suspect in connection with the shooting deaths of two people inside a dorm room on the University of Colorado - Colorado Springs campus, authorities said Monday.

title: Health experts warning of Dengue Fever surge in tropical climates
description: Health experts are warning of an anticipated surge of Dengue Fever in North and South America. The potentially deadly, mosquito-borne disease is currently spreading across Brazil. Dr. Albert Ko, a professor at the Yale School of Public Health, joined CBS News to discuss the illness.

title: Israel says it will launch offensive on Rafah if Hamas doesn't release hostages by Ramadan
description: Israel is vowing to invade Rafah in the southern portion of Gaza if Hamas doesn't release the remaining hostages it's holding by the start of Ramadan on March 10. Much of the Western world, including the U.S., is warning Israel not to launch the offensive. Author and Middle East expert Dan Raviv joined CBS News to discuss the situation in the Middle East.

title: Breaking down the fake elector story on "60 Minutes"
description: A Wisconsin man who cast phony votes for former President Donald Trump in the 2020 election says he was tricked into becoming a fake elector. Andrew Hitt, the former chairman of Wisconsin's Republican Party, told "60 Minutes" correspondent Anderson Cooper he was scared to not take action to help Trump win the election. CBS News election law contributor David Becker has more.

title: Satellite to crash through Earth's atmosphere this week
description: A satellite weighing about as much as an adult male rhinoceros is set to re-enter Earth's atmosphere this week, but scientists don't yet know when or where exactly the return will be.

title: DNA links former U.S. soldier to 1978 murder in Germany, investigators say
description: Investigators say evidence found at the crime scene decades ago matched the DNA of James Patrick Dempsey.

title: More flooding in California with rain expected to continue
description: Another series of storms are causing flooding and mudslides throughout California and could spur tornadoes. CBS News correspondent Carter Evans has more on the conditions on the West Coast. And Jen Carfagno, a meteorologist for The Weather Channel, joined CBS News with the forecast.

title: NASA looking for 4 people to live in Mars simulator
description: Ever wonder what it's like to live on Mars? Now, you can apply to try out life on the Red Planet. Here's how to qualify.

title: Michael J. Fox gets standing ovation after surprise appearance at BAFTAs
description: As the Michael J. Fox was taken to the stage in a wheelchair, fellow actors and audience members gave Fox a rousing ovation.

title: Suspect in double shooting at UCCS in custody
description: A person who is believed to be responsible for the fatal shooting of two people inside a dorm room on the University of Colorado - Colorado Springs campus is under arrest.

title: Biden says he's considering sanctions on Russia over Navalny
description: President Biden has blamed Russian President Vladimir Putin for the death of opposition leader Alexey Navalny.

title: AirCanada chatbot costs airline discount it wrongly offered customer
description: The airline is being held responsible for its website chatbot's promise of a retroactive fare discount worth more than $600.

title: Tumi luggage sale: Save up to 40% this Presidents Day
description: Don't miss these extended Black Friday deals on carry-ons, duffel bags, backpacks and more at Tumi.

title: Aid group stepping in to help at U.S.-Mexico border
description: An aid group known as the Tucson Samaritans and volunteers are doing what they can to provide basic necessities for migrants coming across the U.S.-Mexico border. CBS News immigration reporter Camilo Montoya-Galvez has more on that and the ongoing political maneuvering around immigration.

title: Recapping Trump's legal issues | Feb. 19, 2024
description: Donald Trump will likely appeal the ruling made in his civil fraud case last Friday that would force him to pay over $354 million in fines. Attorney and CBS News campaign reporter Katrina Kaufman has more on where things stand with some of the former president's legal cases.

title: How federal judges are pushing back against Jan. 6 conspiracy theories
description: In a growing number of cases, federal judges in D.C. are using their platform to swat down conspiracy theories perpetuated by some Jan. 6 defendants and their supporters.

title: Trump turning attention to general election, Haley hoping to defy odds in South Carolina primary
description: South Carolina's GOP primary is Saturday, but former President Donald Trump is already looking past it to his likely November matchup with President Biden. Meanwhile, Nikki Haley, Trump's last remaining Republican challenger, is vying for an upset in her home state despite polling behind Trump by 35 points there. CBS News' Caitlin Huey-Burns, Olivia Rinaldi and Taurean Small have more.

title: Houthis claim to shoot down U.S. drone after weekend of self-defense strikes by U.S.
description: Yemen's Iranian-backed Houthi rebels say they shot down a U.S. drone and severely damaged a British-owned cargo ship in a missile attack early Monday morning. This comes after a series of self-defense strikes by the U.S. military over the weekend on Houthi targets. CBS News national security correspondent David Martin has more.

title: Abraham Lincoln pardoned Biden's great-great-granddad, documents show
description: President Biden's great-great-grandfather, Moses Robinette, was charged with attempted murder after a fight in 1864.

title: Sleep expert on why people should prioritize sleep quality over quantity
description: According to Shelby Harris, while the duration of sleep is crucial, the quality of that sleep is equally, if not more, important for maintaining heart health.

title: 2 officers, 1 paramedic killed in Minnesota shooting
description: Two police officers and a paramedic were shot and killed early Sunday in Burnsville, Minnesota, a Twin Cities suburb. Officials say they were responding to a man barricaded with children in a home. CBS News Minnesota reporter Marielle Mohs has more.

title: Pilot of packed boat that sank in English Channel convicted of manslaughter
description: A man who allegedly told a small boat overloaded with migrants that he'd get them to the U.K. "or kill you all" has been convicted of manslaughter.

title: Alexey Navalny's widow calls on supporters to stand with her in fight against Putin
description: Yulia Navalnaya, the widow of Alexey Navalny, vowed on Monday to carry on her husband's work to bring about "a free, peaceful, happy Russia" and called on his followers to rally alongside her follownig his death in a Russian prison camp.

title: Palestinian foreign minister tells U.N.'s top court Israeli occupation must come to "total end"
description: The International Court of Justice in the Netherlands has started its hearings into Israel's occupation of Palestinian territories, with the Palestinian foreign minister accusing Israel of genocide and telling the U.N.'s top court the occupation must come to an "unconditional and total end."

title: 2/19: CBS Morning News
description: Countdown to South Carolina Republican primary; George Santos sues Jimmy Kimmel over Cameo videos.

title: The Atlanta airport angel who wouldn't take no for an answer
description: With a torn ACL and a knee in need of replacement, Cindy Tutko was in pain as she walked with a heavy bag through the Atlanta airport. Then she met a good Samaritan who became like a son to her.

title: Super cities showdown: Kansas City vs. San Francisco
description: In a CBS Mornings annual tradition, Michelle Miller and Dana Jacobson go on a head-to-head battle to see which Super Bowl contender has the superior hometown.

title: Here's what's open and closed on Presidents Day, from Costco to banks
description: Presidents Day is a major shopping day in the U.S., but some consumers may find some services closed on February 19.

title: Trump fraud ruling adds to his string of legal losses in New York
description: Former President Donald Trump and his company have been winless in a series of costly, cascading high-profile legal battles in New York in the last 14 months.

title: Fallout from Navalny's death continues; Biden confident about Ukraine aid package vote
description: Human rights groups are reporting the arrests of hundreds of Russians mourning the death of longtime opposition leader Alexey Navalny. Russian officials say Navalny died last week in an Arctic penal colony. CBS News foreign correspondent Imtiaz Tyab has more on Navalny and CBS News White House reporter Willie James Inman has more on an aid package in Congress that would send money to Ukraine for their fight against Vladimir Putin.

title: Top moments from 2024 People's Choice Awards
description: Greta Gerwig's "Barbie" movie took home big wins, as did Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce. Here are the top moments from the night.

title: Biden to give chip maker $1.5 billion to expand U.S. production
description: GlobalFoundries intends to use funding to help pay for construction of new advanced chip factory in Malta, New York,  and revitalize its plant in Burlington, Vermont.

title: Dr. Sue Varma on about the benefits of optimism, and how to become more optimistic
description: Dr. Sue Varma joins “CBS Mornings” to talk about her new book, “Practical Optimism,”' and her insights from experiences as medical director of the World Trade Center Mental Health Program. She also discusses how a person can become more optimistic.

title: Mielle Organics founder Monique Rodriguez on growing a company out of tragedy
description: Monique Rodriguez, the powerhouse behind Mielle Organics, joins ”CBS Mornings” to talk about how she started her brand from her kitchen nearly a decade ago and is now in over 100,000 stores worldwide.

title: How a simple act of kindness connected two strangers at Atlanta airport
description: In a world often divided, the story of Cindy Tutko and a kind stranger at the Atlanta airport serves as a heartwarming reminder of the power of human connection. When Tutko was struggling to reach her gate due to a limp, an unexpected offer of help arrived. David Begnaud has their story.

title: How improving sleep can mean better cardiac health
description: In recognition of American Heart Month, sleep expert Shelby Harris sheds light on the link between poor sleep and its effects on heart health.

title: Wife of fallen Burnsville police officer Paul Elmstrand: "He had to do what he thought was right"
description: The wife of Burnsville police officer Paul Elmstrand — one of the three first responders killed over the weekend — said he would "drop everything" to help out someone in need.

title: U.N.'s top court considering legality of Israel's occupation of West Bank
description: Historic meetings are now underway on the legality of Israel​'s decades-long occupation of lands sought for a Palestinian​ state.

title: New York man running "Breaking Bad-style drug lab" pleads guilty
description: Matthew Leshinsky was "operating a Breaking Bad-style drug lab and tried to conceal it under the guise of a legitimate business," the district attorney said.

title: Is tax preparation software worth it? Here's what some experts think
description: Tax software can help you file your tax returns quickly and affordably, but it's not right the choice for everyone.

title: Alexey Navalny's widow says Russia is "hiding his body"
description: Russian officials say leading opposition figure Alexey Navalny suffered "sudden death syndrome" in prison.

title: What will the 2024 spring homebuying season look like?
description: Spring is likely to bring more homes to the market — and more homebuyers interested in purchasing them.

title: Royal Caribbean's newest cruise ship aims to reduce food waste with AI technology
description: Amid environmentalists' calls for the cruise industry to minimize waste, Royal Caribbean is introducing the use of artificial intelligence to tackle food waste on its latest and largest vessel, the "Icon of the Seas."

title: Over 30 million people on flood watch in California
description: As a series of powerful storms sweeps through California, over 30 million residents face flood watches amid growing concerns over flash flooding potential mudslides.

title: Eye Opener: Another atmospheric river hits California with more rain and snow
description: In California, a new atmospheric river brings more rain and snow to areas still reeling from recent storms. Also, two Minnesota police officers and a paramedic are killed in a shootout with a man barricaded in a suburban home full of kids. All that and all that matters in today’s Eye Opener.

title: Three first responders killed in shootout in Minnesota
description: Two police officers and a paramedic were killed following a shootout with an armed man who had barricaded himself and seven children in a home in Burnsville, Minnesota. The suspect was later found dead.

title: Mystery still surrounds circumstances of Alexey Navalny’s death in Russian prison
description: More than 350 people were arrested over the weekend in Russia as they mourned the death of opposition leader Alexey Navalny in a prison camp. Russian officials say he died suddenly but they have not released his body or announced the cause of his death.

title: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu vows to “finish the job” against Hamas
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu vows to "finish the job" of destroying Hamas and rescuing hostages as Israeli forces gears up for a possible ground assault in Rafah, in southern Gaza.

title: A look at Trump's mounting legal troubles as South Carolina Republican primary nears
description: With the South Carolina Republican presidential primary looming, former President Donald Trump is facing more legal troubles after he is ordered by a New York City court to pay over $350 million in penalties for fraud.

title: Experts reject "impossible project" to rebuild exterior of a pyramid
description: An expert committee commissioned to review a contentious plan to reconstruct the outside of Giza's smallest pyramid says "there is no way" it can happen.

title: 12 alleged cartel members killed in clashes near U.S. border
description: The clashes happened in the same area where four U.S. citizens, two of whom later died, were kidnapped at gunpoint last year.

title: U.S. man admits to rape, murder of fellow tourist near German castle
description: A Michigan man has admitted to the rape and murder of a fellow U.S. tourist near a picturesque castle in southern Germany.

title: Are morning or night workouts better? Here's what experts say.
description: What's the best time for working out: morning, afternoon or evening? The answer isn't what you may think.

title: Are there mattresses smaller than a twin?
description: There are a few mattress sizes that are smaller than twin. Learn more about small single and toddler mattresses.

title: How to watch the rescheduled Daytona 500 today: Starting time, lineup, livestream options, more
description: Gear up to the watch the rescheduled 2024 Daytona 500 and find out how stream the race even if you don't have cable.

title: 1 killed, 5 wounded in shooting at Waffle House in Indianapolis, police say
description: One of the wounded was in critical condition, police said, adding that the gunfire was apparently the result of a dispute between two groups.

title: Chicago man killed in second house fire in same home
description: Family says the man was not home the first time a fire broke out.

title: How Los Angeles is building new EV chargers fast
description: The U.S. has big plans to make EV charging available across the country, but that effort is moving slowly. CBS News environmental correspondent David Schechter explores the problem and innovative solutions to improve charging capacity right now.

title: "Oppenheimer" wins best picture at the British Academy Film Awards
description: Atom bomb epic "Oppenheimer" won seven prizes, including best picture, at the British Academy Film Awards.

title: 2/18/2024: Crisis in the Red Sea; Fake Electors; Finding Cillian Murphy
description: First, an inside look at the U.S. Navy response to Houthi Red Sea attacks. Then, a Trump fake elector in Wisconsin speaks out. And, Cillian Murphy: The 60 Minutes Interview.

title: Trump fake elector in Wisconsin describes how he says he was tricked | 60 Minutes
description: Andrew Hitt, who signed a phony electoral certificate for former President Trump in 2020, tells 60 Minutes that he and other Wisconsin Republican electors were tricked.

title: Cillian Murphy's first reaction to "Oppenheimer" script
description: Actor Cillian Murphy shares the first thing he told writer-director Christopher Nolan after reading the "Oppenheimer" script.

title: Cillian Murphy on turning off his characters
description: Actor Cillian Murphy says it takes time to decompress after playing a character. "For a few weeks, you just don't know what to do with all this energy and this focus."

title: How David Bowie helped inspire the portrayal of Robert Oppenheimer
description: "It is possible that this is the first time that David Bowie has been compared to Robert Oppenheimer," Scott Pelley commented to Cillian Murphy. Murphy says he found similarities between the two men.

title: Cillian Murphy on his legacy
description: Cillian Murphy says it's too soon to talk about his acting legacy, adding he's hungry for more.

title: Emily Blunt on a deleted scene from "Oppenheimer"
description: Actor Emily Blunt tells Scott Pelley that in a deleted moment from "Oppenheimer," she slaps Cillian Murphy.

title: Mexico sets up checkpoint near border fence gap after migrants cross into U.S.
description: Migrants in Mexico have moved on to another border crossing after Mexico's government set up a checkpoint near a fence gap known as the San Judas Break.

title: What Russian opposition leader Alexey Navalny told 60 Minutes in 2020
description: Alexey Navalny, Russia's most prominent opposition leader, died at his arctic prison. In 2020, while recovering from poisoning, he spoke with 60 Minutes.

title: Cillian Murphy: The 60 Minutes Interview
description: “Oppenheimer” star Cillian Murphy pulled back the curtain to talk about his approach to acting.

title: Nonprofit provides culinary training and free meals
description: Farming Hope, a nonprofit in San Francisco, provides culinary training for those who have been incarcerated, experienced homelessness or been the victims of violent crime. On top of that, all the meals that are served are free, providing a much-needed lifeline for those experiencing food insecurity. CBS Bay Area's Itay Hod has the story.

title: Congresswomen push to change rules to make it easier for mothers to serve
description: Two representatives are pushing for a rule change that would make it easier for new mothers to serve in Congress. The new rules would allow mothers to vote by proxy from home for the first six weeks after giving birth. Scott MacFarlane has the story.

title: Threat of gun violence stressing out Americans
description: The pervasive threat of gun violence in the U.S. is stressing out Americans, according to the American Psychological Association. About one-third of Americans say they've changed their behavior because of mass shootings and about 75% of Americans report significant stress following a mass shooting, APA CEO Arthur Evans said. Mark Strassmann has more.

title: Haley facing polling deficit in home state
description: Former U.S. Ambassador to the U.N. Nikki Haley is trailing former President Trump by about 35 points in North Carolina, where she once served as governor, with less than a week to go before the state's primary. Skyler Henry reports.

title: 2 officers, 1 paramedic shot dead in Minnesota
description: Two police officers and one paramedic were shot and killed in Burnsville, Minnesota, on Sunday. The person who shot them is also dead, authorities said. CBS Minnesota's Jonah Kaplan reports.

title: Israel pressing ahead with Rafah offensive
description: Israel has vowed to press ahead with a ground offensive into the southern Gaza city of Rafah, where more than 1.5 million people, many of them displaced because of the war, are now living. Holly Williams has the latest.

title: Cillian Murphy on acting and his first reaction to "Oppenheimer" script
description: In an interview with 60 Minutes, Cillian Murphy speaks candidly with Scott Pelley about his life and work.

title: Michigan's 2020 Democratic electors take on "fake electors"
description: Legitimate Democratic electors in Michigan told Anderson Cooper why they filed a lawsuit against the "fake electors" in the state.

title: One U.S. Navy secret weapon in the Red Sea? Sailor morale
description: On the USS Eisenhower, one of the strategies in the Red Sea fight against the Houthis is increasing morale by making soldiers feel part of something bigger than themselves.

title: Cillian Murphy said yes to "Oppenheimer" before reading a script
description: Cillian Murphy, who became a household name with "Oppenheimer," said yes to the role before reading a script. He's been in six Christopher Nolan films and says that saying yes to the director pays off.

title: Cillian Murphy on his preparation, instinct he uses when acting
description: "Oppenheimer" star Cillian Murphy pulled back the curtain to talk about his approach to acting.

title: Wisconsin fake elector explains why he went along with the plan
description: Andrew Hitt, a fake elector who signed a phony electoral certificate after the 2020 election, said he was tricked.

title: Navy three-star admiral discusses the mission to stop Houthi attacks
description: With backing from Iran, the Houthi militia in Yemen have kept up a barrage of attacks on ships in the Red Sea for months. The U.S. military is pushing back.

title: U.S. Navy destroyers target Houthi Red Sea missiles and drones
description: For months, the U.S. Navy has operated out of the Red Sea at a pace not seen in decades, as the military responds to Houthi targeting of commercial ships. Norah 'O'Donnell reports.

title: Wisconsin fake elector on why he signed phony electoral document for Trump
description: Andrew Hitt, who signed a phony electoral certificate for former President Trump in 2020, tells 60 Minutes that he and other Wisconsin Republican electors were tricked.
